description: The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in securities of the index. The index generally consists of securities issued by exchange-traded funds (“ETFs”) and is split into two components, with a 50% allocation to fixed income and equity ETFs (the “Core Portfolio”) and a 50% allocation to ETFs of 12 asset categories (the “Explore Portfolio”).
name: Strategy Shares Nasdaq 5 Handl Index ETF
